THE was arrested in Betania in KwaZulu Natal after he was found with 467
images of child pornography on his tablet and cell phone. The Port Shepstone Regional Court sentenced Bret Allen
Steven (46) to 10 years imprisonment for possession of child pornography. Steven was arrested on 30 March by the Child Protection and
Sexual Offences Unit specialising in Serial and Electronic Crimes
Investigation. “He was taken to the Port Shepstone police station for
detention and his devices were confiscated,”police spokesperson Colonel
Thembeka Mbele. He then appeared in court where he was convicted and
sentenced to 10 years imprisonment with five years suspended. The court also declared unfit to possess a firearm and his
name will be included in the National Register for Sex Offenders. 